    "eventMetadata": {
      "context_description": "Ukraine's Verkhovna Rada extended martial law and general mobilization on August 8 for 90 days until November 9, 2024, maintaining the constitutional prohibition on presidential and parliamentary elections during wartime. President Zelenskyy's five-year term expired May 20 but continues under legal provisions barring polls amid the Russian invasion, citing security risks for millions of displaced voters, soldiers at the front, and logistical hurdles. Officials have ruled out snap elections, prioritizing defense over campaigning. Public polls show divided sentiment, but the next parliamentary vote on extensions in early November could signal timelines for post-war polls, likely in 2025 or later.",
      "context_requires_regen": false,
      "context_updated_at": "2026-03-26T06:48:22.014Z"
